"decimal integers.  This qualifier means there must be at least *m* "
"repetitions, and at most *n*.  For example, ``a/{1,3}b`` will match ``a/b``, "
"``a//b``, and ``a///b``.  It won't match ``ab``, which has no slashes, or "
"``a////b``, which has four."
